    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the grill to high, then crush your <strong>cardamom</strong> <strong>pod[s]</strong> open by squashing them with the side of a knife</p><p>Add your <strong>basmati rice</strong>, <strong>crushed cardamom pod[s] </strong>and 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>cold</strong> <strong>water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat, once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked, once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/paneer-tikka-masala-with-cardamom-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Line a baking tray with <strong>tin foil</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>paneer</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>paneer </strong>to a bowl with <strong>half</strong> your <strong>natural yoghurt</strong>, <strong>half</strong> your <strong>curry powder </strong>and <strong>half </strong>your<strong> ginger paste </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Give everything a good mix up and then add<strong> </strong>to the tray and put under the grill for 15 min or until cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>paneer tikka</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/paneer-tikka-masala-with-cardamom-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice your<strong> shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> roughly</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/paneer-tikka-masala-with-cardamom-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced shallot</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 5-6 min or until caramelised</p><p>Once caramelised, add the <strong>chopped tomato</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/paneer-tikka-masala-with-cardamom-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add the <strong>remaining curry powder</strong>, <strong>remaining ginger paste</strong>, your <strong>tomato</strong> <strong>paste</strong>, <strong>ground</strong> <strong>paprika</strong> and the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> to the pan with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar </strong>and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>flour</strong></p><p>Cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/paneer-tikka-masala-with-cardamom-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[250ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>with your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>and your <strong>clotted cream</strong></p><p>Cook for a further 5 min or until the sauce begins to thicken to a gravy-like consistency</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/paneer-tikka-masala-with-cardamom-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the sauce has thickened, stir through the <strong>paneer tikka </strong>and your <strong>garam masala </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>paneer</strong> <strong>tikka</strong> <strong>masala</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/paneer-tikka-masala-with-cardamom-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>paneer</strong> <strong>tikka</strong> <strong>masala</strong> with the <strong>cardamom</strong> <strong>rice</strong> to the side</p><p>Drizzle over the <strong>remaining natural yoghurt</strong></p><p>Tip: Watch out for any cardamom pods!</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
